<HEADLINE>
FT  05 AUG 93 / W German industrial orders fell by 1.6 per cent in June
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JUDY DEMPSEY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BERLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
West German industrial orders fell by 1.6 per cent in June compared with
May, writes Judy Dempsey in Berlin. However, demand for consumer goods rose
1.5 per cent. The federal economics ministry said a 3.7 per cent decline in
capital goods was largely to blame for the greater than expected fall in
industrial orders.
Foreign orders fell only 0.9 per cent, but economists are concerned about
the impact on exports of last weekend's changes to the ERM.
