<HEADLINE>
FT  04 AUG 93 / International Company News: Donohue returns to black
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
DONOHUE, a large eastern Canada newsprint producer controlled by the
Quebecor publishing and printing group, returned to profitability in the
first half with earnings of CDollars 8.3m (Dollars 6.4m), or 23 cents a
share, against a loss of Dollars 11.3m, or 36 cents, a year earlier. Sales
were up 13 per cent to Dollars 286m.
Second-quarter net profit was Dollars 2m, or 5 cents a share, against a loss
of Dollars 3m, or 10 cents.
Newsprint and timber products shipments were higher with firm prices but
pulp markets declined further. Lower interest rates and a lower Canadian
dollar helped - most of Donohue's production goes to the US.
Canfor, a western Canada forest products group, earned CDollars 17.6m, or 60
cents a share, in the second quarter, against a loss of Dollars 9.1m, or 34
cents. Revenues were up 10 per cent to Dollars 301m. First-half profit
equalled Dollars 1.17 a share, against a loss of 78 cents.
Tembex, an eastern Canada special pulp and cartonboard producer, had a
CDollars 6.7m third-quarter loss, against a loss of Dollars 4.3m. The loss
for nine months was Dollars 34m, against a loss of Dollars 22.7m, on sales
of Dollars 277m, against Dollars 223m.
</TEXT>
