signalled earlier this year when it said it intended to bring down group net
borrowings to SKr5bn-SKr6bn. The investment group, which has majority or
leading stakes in many of Sweden's top companies, slipped to a SKr542m loss
in the first quarter. Group net debt stood at SKr9.86bn at March 31.
The Wallenbergs have avoided any significant erosion of their control in
Swedish industry in spite of the trading difficulties.
