FT  04 AUG 93 / UK Company News: Senior management changes at Archer
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AJ Archer, the listed Lloyd's agency, has announced a reorganisation of
senior management and the closure of two of its 19 syndicates.
Mr Richard Maylam will stand down as chairman of AJ Archer Holdings in order
to focus on his primary responsibility as underwriter of syndicate 270. Mr
Brian Kellett will become executive chairman and Mr Ralph Sharp will be
group managing director.
Syndicate 697 will merge with syndicate 741 for the 1994 year of account.
Syndicate 256 will cease to underwrite from 1994. AJ Archer &amp; Co, one of two
managing agents in the group, will be renamed Tower Underwriting Agents. AJ
Archer Holdings will be renamed at a later stage.
</TEXT>
