FT  04 AUG 93 / UK Company News: CE Heath raises Pounds 21m in share sale
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CE HEATH and CE Heath International Holdings yesterday announced the
successful completion of the placing of 32.4m HIH shares held by Risk
Management Holdings, a wholly owned subsidiary of Heath.
HIH is the Australian holding company which owns Heath's underwriting
operations in Australasia and the Pacific Basin and was, until its flotation
on the Australian stock exchange in June 1992, a subsidiary of Heath.
Following its listing Heath's interest was reduced to below 50 per cent.
Yesterday's placing left the insurance broking group with just 25 per cent
of the company.
The shares have been placed by MacQuarie Equities with a number of
institutional investors worldwide at ADollars 1.40 apiece, against their
last traded price of ADollars 1.42.
The placing will raise some Pounds 21m before tax, against a book value at
March 31 of about Pounds 14.3m. Of the net proceeds, Pounds 11m will be used
to reduce bank borrowings. The balance will be used to fund expansion.
</TEXT>
