FT  04 AUG 93 / Tory MPs warn against British involvement in Bosnia air
strikes
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The reaction of some Tory MPs suggested that British involvement in air
strikes would risk opening fresh divisions in the party, David Owen writes.
Mr Nicholas Budgen, MP for Wolverhampton South-West, said: 'We should
declare that there is no British national interest at stake here . . ., that
the best way we can contribute to future peace is to withdraw our forces and
emphasise to the contestants that their future lies in their own hands.'
Mr John Wilkinson, MP for Ruislip Northwood, said he was 'sceptical' about
the efficacy of air strikes. 'I think it would heighten Serb intransigence
and probably lead to retaliation against our troops.' But Mr Patrick
Cormack, MP for Staffordshire South, said: 'I believe we should have taken
firm action a long, long time ago.'
