<HEADLINE>
FT  04 AUG 93 / Strike disrupts mail service
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE POSTAL service in Cardiff was seriously disrupted last night after 900
workers went on indefinite strike over new working arrangements.
About 5,000 bags of mail were lying unsorted at Royal Mail's Penarth Road
headquarters as managers sealed about 2,500 post boxes in the city and
outlying districts.
The decision to extend an earlier 24-hour stoppage came after a meeting
called by the Union of Communication Workers. The union says a system of
fixed shift patterns would force many postal staff to work unsocial hours
permanently.
Mr Steve Bell, the union's Cardiff branch secretary, said: 'These new
working hours would have a disastrous effect on the social lives of many of
our members.'
Managers said the sides had been close to agreement before talks were broken
off and that more than 75 per cent of staff in south Wales and the
south-west were working the new system.
</TEXT>
