<HEADLINE>
FT  04 AUG 93 / World Trade News: Boost for Yemen oil exports
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ADEN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The first cargo will be shipped today from a new oil field expected to boost
Yemen's exports by two-thirds, oil industry sources said yesterday, Reuter
reports from Aden.
They said the 550,000 barrel shipment from the Masila field in the eastern
Hadramaut region was being transferred to the refinery at the al-Shihr
terminal on the Gulf of Aden. The Masila project is a joint venture between
Canadian Occidental Petroleum, which holds 52 per cent, Pecten Yemen, a US
subsidiary of Royal Dutch/Shell, with 20 per cent, Occidental of the US with
18 per cent and Lebanese Contractors International, 10 per cent.
