FT  03 AUG 93 / International Company News: Amsterdam to delist shares in
Daf
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RONALD VAN DE KROL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   AMSTERDAM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SHARES in Daf, the Dutch truckmaker which collapsed in early 1993, are to be
delisted from the Amsterdam stock exchange on September 1, with official
trading to end on August 31, the bourse said yesterday, writes Ronald van de
Krol in Amsterdam.
The shares are now quoted at Fl 0.45, compared with their flotation price of
Fl 47 in mid-1989. Shareholders include the Dutch state, the Flemish
regional government of Belgium, and several institutional shareholders.
