<HEADLINE>
FT  03 AUG 93 / UK Company News: Govett to acquire US trust for Dollars 3.8m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN, Personal Finance Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GOVETT &amp; Company, the fund management group, has agreed to buy the North
American Trust Company for Dollars 3.8m (Pounds 2.55m) from the Bank of San
Diego.
The trust company provides pension trust services to law firms and medical
services groups in the US and currently administers some Dollars 1.4bn of
assets. Govett already has a Jersey-based trust company, London Pacific.
Mr Ian Whitehead, chief financial officer, said the purchase gave Govett the
administrative and operating capability to manage trust accounts for high
net worth individuals, and allowed it the chance to cross-sell its
investment management services. Trust companies are a source of high quality
earnings, he said.
The agreement is subject to regulatory approval which is expected to be
granted within six to eight weeks.
