<HEADLINE>
FT  03 AUG 93 / UK Company News: Scottish National
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The split capital Scottish National Trust had a net asset value of 67.3p per
capital share at June 30.
The figure marked a sharp recovery from the value of 21.9p a year earlier
and just 2.8p at the trust's September year-end.
Net revenue for the nine months to end-June declined to Pounds 9.24m (Pounds
11.32m), equivalent to earnings of 5.11p (6.44p) per income share. A third
interim dividend of 1.8p reduces the total so far to 4.9p (5.8p).
</TEXT>
