<HEADLINE>
FT  03 AUG 93 / Observer: Adding up
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
If a pair of dinosaurs had purchased a 100-million-year life annuity paying
out Dollars 416.66 each month, how much dosh would their heirs have received
to date?
The answer is half a trillion dollars (Dollars 500bn), which is also the
value of the assets Merrill Lynch now holds in custody on behalf of its
clients worldwide. Celebrating this target achieved earlier in the year, the
American broker has been holding an internal competition to see who could
make sense of such a big number.
So far, Observer's favourite calculation is the one that concludes that half
a trillion is the sum the American Indians would today find in their cash
management account had they invested the Dollars 24 received for the sale of
Manhattan at a rate of 6.69 per cent per annum.
</TEXT>
